{
  "texts": [
    "Layer normalization and GELU activation are also inserted, as illustrated in Fig. 4.Finally, given the high-resolution mask features F hr and output token T, the mask prediction M hr in high-resolution of 512 × 512 can be obtained:M hr = F hr ⊙ M LP hr (T),(7)where M LP hr is also a three-layer MLP.",
    "M LP hr projects T and reduces its dimension to 16.",
    "Loss FunctionSince ELE-SAM predicts bi-resolution results, we apply supervision for both of them to ensure coarse-to-fine mask evolution.",
    "In particular, given lowresolution prediction M lr and high-resolution prediction M hr, we calculate the Dice loss [37] for each resolution level with ground-truth M GT.",
    "The total loss L equals to the Dice loss from two resolution levels plus the loss L PA from prompt adapter, which is formulated as:L = L Dice (M lr, M GT) + L Dice (M hr, M GT) + L PA.(8) ELE-40K BenchmarkThe increasing demand for electric power has highlighted the importance for monitoring the power transmission corridors and maintaining transmission safety."
  ]
}